		<h2 class="article-excerpt" itemprop="alternativeHeadline">These are today's best ideas</h2>
		<p><strong>1. <a href="http://www.bostonglobe.com/opinion/2015/05/06/mother-day-perfect-time-rethink-our-social-construct-motherhood/uVxz4i8aQVQwfvPV2L9k3O/story.html" target="_blank">Motherhood is a cultural invention. It might be time to rethink it.</a></strong></p>
<p>By Kathleen McCartney in the Boston Globe</p>
<p><strong>2. <a href="http://www.edtechmagazine.com/higher/article/2015/05/social-scientists-new-data-dilemma" target="_blank">You should want Facebook to give away your data.</a></strong></p>
<p>By Tara E. Buck in EdTech</p>
<p><strong>3. <a href="http://www.pri.org/stories/2015-04-30/do-we-all-have-alzhemers-completely-wrong-man-says-yes" target="_blank">Do we have Alzheimer&rsquo;s completely wrong?</a></strong></p>
<p>By Turna Ray at Science Friday</p>
<p><strong>4. <a href="http://allafrica.com/stories/201505060536.html" target="_blank">On the brink of becoming Ebola-free, Liberia should embrace its survivors.</a></strong></p>
<p>By AllAfrica</p>
<p><strong>5. <a href="http://nationswell.com/im-stuck-app-tracks-traffic-jams-delays/" target="_blank">Can an app improve America&rsquo;s crumbling infrastructure?</a></strong></p>
<p>By Ashley Tate in NationSwell</p>
<p><a href="http://aspen.us/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter size-portrait_small_2x wp-image-123195" src="http://timedotcom.files.wordpress.com/2014/07/aspen61.png" alt="" width="100%" /></a><em><a href="http://www.aspeninstitute.org/" target="_blank">The Aspen Institute</a> is an educational and policy studies organization based in Washington, D.C.</em></p>

