n transferred from the Hospital of Sassari to he National Institute for Infectious Diseases (INMI) Lazzaro Spallanzani of Rome in a special aircraft.<\/p>\n<p>Since the patient did not start experiencing symptoms until 72 hours after returning to Italy, WHO says it is not necessary to conduct contact tracing of individuals who were on the same plane. Ebola can only be transmitted via the bodily fluids of a symptomatic person.<\/p>\n<p>More than 26,720 cases of Ebola have been reported in Sierra Leone, Liberia and Guinea since the start of the outbreak, and more than 11,000 people have died.<\/p>\n<div class=\"galleryContainer galleryContainer--embedded\" data-gallery=\"3507162\" data-size=\"default\"><\/div>\n","read_more":true,"section":{"name":"Health","slug":"health","url":"http:\/\/time.com\/health\/","description":"The latest health news, trends, and commentary from TIME, covering medicine, mental health, diet, fitness, sex, aging, disease, healthcare, policy and more","health":true},"tag":{"name":"ebola","slug":"ebola","url":"http:\/\/time.com\/tag\/ebola\/"},"tags":"ebola|ebola africa|ebola doctors|ebola italy|Ebola outbreak|Ebola patient|Guinea|health care worker|Italy|Liberia|patient|Sierra Leone","hero":{"class":"landscape","thumbnail":"https:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2015\/05\/128624230-1-copy.jpg?quality=65&strip=color&w=100&h=100&crop=1","src":{"small":"https:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2015\/05\/128624230-1-copy.jpg?quality=65&strip=color&w=280","small_2x":"https:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2015\/05\/128624230-1-copy.jpg?quality=65&strip=color&w=560","large":"https:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2015\/05\/128624230-1-copy.jpg?quality=65&strip=color&w=550","large_2x":"https:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2015\/05\/128624230-1-copy.jpg?quality=65&strip=color&w=1100"},"credit":"Getty Images","caption":"","alt":"128624230","providers":[],"masonry":{"small_width":300,"small_height":234,"large_width":625,"large_height":487