ow that although Crozier&#8217;s blood had been declared Ebola-free, his eye was still full of the virus. Not only that, but the iris turned from blue to green.<\/p>\n<p>&ldquo;It felt almost personal that the virus could be in my eye without me knowing it,&rdquo; he said, adding that the color change felt &#8220;like an assault.&#8221; Dr. Crozier&#8217;s sight and eye color later returned, mystifying doctors who had been helping treat his eye inflammation called uveitis, but his case shows researchers there is still much to learn about the deadly virus.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/www.nytimes.com\/2015\/05\/08\/health\/weeks-after-his-recovery-ebola-lurked-in-a-doctors-eye.html\" target=\"_blank\">Read more at the New York <em>Times<\/em>.<\/a><\/p>\n<div class=\"galleryContainer galleryContainer--embedded\" data-gallery=\"3507162\" data-size=\"default\"><\/div>\n","read_more":true,"section":{"name":"Health","slug":"health","url":"http:\/\/time.com\/health\/","description":"The latest health news, trends, and commentary from TIME, covering medicine, mental health, diet, fitness, sex, aging, disease, healthcare, policy and more","health":true},"topic":{"name":"Ebola","slug":"ebola-2","left_rail_title":"All Content","left_rail_subhead":"Ebola","editor_content":"","url":"http:\/\/time.com\/topic\/ebola-2\/","email_title":"Ebola | TIME","email_body":"Ebola%0A%0Ahttp%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2Ftopic%2Febola-2%2F","encoded_url":"http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F%2Ftag%2Febola%2F","encoded_shortlink":"","twitter_text":"","encoded_title":"Ebola","is_vault":false},"tag":{"name":"ebola","slug":"ebola","url":"http:\/\/time.com\/tag\/ebola\/"},"tags":"Blue|Dr. Ian Crozier|ebola|eye color|green|NEJM","id":3850998,"encoded_url":"http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3850998%2Febola-eye-virus-ian-crozier%2F","encoded_shortlink":"http%3A%2F%2Fti.me%2F1F8v9Zi","encoded_title":"Doctors+Stumped+After+Ebola+Survivor%E2%80%99s+Eye+Changed+Colors","galleries":[{"id":3507162,"slug":"inside-ebola-crisis-moving-photogr