age, Kenema, Sierra Leone. <br><br><\/b>\"I arrived to Langtown village, Sierra Leone,with a team of volunteers from Kenema governmental hospital. They were there to bury Baindu-Koruma a female victim of the Ebola virus. Everyone was silent. She had been dead for two days, and everyone was terrified of going inside. As the volunteers left with the body, her husband, Idriss Koruma (who can be seen center) and relatives burst into tears. They had only realized then, it seemed, that she was gone.\nThe photo moved me because I felt helpless for the man \u2013 having a loved one laying on a bed but you can't say goodbye, as this is the least a human could do for one last time, but in a situation like this you can't because you'll probably get the virus and die as well.\"","credit":"Mohammed Elshamy\u2014Anadolu\/Getty Images","alt":"Idrissa-koruma, a 35 year old man, the husband of Baindu-koruma a 28 year old woman, grives her death of Ebola deadly virus.","width":1500,"height":1001,"orientation":"square","url":"http:\/\/time.com\/3507162\/inside-ebola-crisis-moving-photographs\/photo\/mohammed-elshamy-ebola\/","encoded_url":"http:\/\/time.com\/3507162\/inside-ebola-crisis-moving-photographs\/photo\/mohammed-elshamy-ebola\/","twitter_via":"TIMEHealth","encoded_title":"Inside+the+Ebola+Crisis%3A+The+Images+that+Moved+them+Most","encoded_shortlink":"http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3507162%2Finside-ebola-crisis-moving-photographs%2Fphoto%2Fmohammed-elshamy-ebola%2F","twitter_encoded_shortlink":"http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3507162%2Finside-ebola-crisis-moving-photographs%2Fphoto%2Fmohammed-elshamy-ebola%2F","email_title":"Inside%20the%20Ebola%20Crisis%3A%20The%20Images%20that%20Moved%20them%20Most","twitter_text":"See%20inside%20the%20Ebola%20crisis%3A%20the%20images%20that%20moved%20them%20most","fb_text":"See%20inside%20the%20Ebola%20crisis%3A%20the%20images%20that%20moved%20them%20most","email_body":"Inside%20the%20Ebola%20Crisis%3A%20The%20Images%20that%20Moved%20them%20Most%0A%0Aht